Blades of Law - Povar</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukarakastp2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>karakasTP2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/29/02 10:57:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31343.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> CoH'ing down to the safe hall entrance can save some time, however if your raid force is not strong enough to clear down safely, then I doubt you'll be able to clear the royals area anyway.<br>
<br>
As for pulling the King room, I do the following:<br>
<br>
* raid force waits in old herbalist room<br>
* tagger waits fd in hallway outside herbalist room<br>
* puller missiles guard in king room<br>
* mage (sitting at far end of herbalist room) immediately casts coh<br>
* puller runs up the ramp, turns corner, hits stonestance, and waits for coh to land<br>
* tagger waits for king to leave, then tags what is left<br>
* raid force invis's to king room, mezzes remaining adds, burns down king<br>
<br>
For the Queen room, I do the following:<br>
<br>
* raid force waits at back of king room<br>
* faction mule waits in the hallway outside herbalist room<br>
* puller missiles guard in queen room <br>
* mage (sitting at far end of king room) immediately casts coh<br>
* puller runs up the ramp to faction mule, waits for coh to land<br>
* faction mule hails queen while her guards wander home<br>
* raid force rushes queen room and kills her guards<br>
* faction mule lets queen wander home<br>
* MA pins queen in corner, her back to raid, raid burns her down<br>
<br>
